I wonder if you could
mention an example of this.

00:40:20.336 --> 00:40:21.460
PETER GODFREY-SMITH: Right.

00:40:21.460 --> 00:40:26.920
So once you get to
animals, genuine junctions

00:40:26.920 --> 00:40:28.180
tend not to occur.

00:40:28.180 --> 00:40:30.850
But in single-celled
life, so in bacteria,

00:40:30.850 --> 00:40:32.690
you have a quite
different shape.

00:40:32.690 --> 00:40:35.950
I mean, the tree metaphor
or the tree model

00:40:35.950 --> 00:40:40.540
doesn't apply particularly
well to bacteria.

00:40:40.540 --> 00:40:43.810
They're continually exchanging
bits and pieces of DNA

00:40:43.810 --> 00:40:45.845
in a kind of freeway.

00:40:45.845 --> 00:40:49.330
The eukaryotic cells
that make up our bodies

00:40:49.330 --> 00:40:51.460
are the products
of an event where

00:40:51.460 --> 00:40:57.730
one ancient prokaryotic
cell essentially swallowed

00:40:57.730 --> 00:41:01.310
another and the two of them
came to live as a unit.

00:41:01.310 --> 00:41:05.190
So that's a kind of
merging in the tree where

00:41:05.190 --> 00:41:08.650
all the cells in your body are
descended from a merging event

00:41:08.650 --> 00:41:11.710
that took place probably
perhaps something like 1.8

00:41:11.710 --> 00:41:15.160
billion years or so ago.

00:41:15.160 --> 00:41:18.190
So if you think about the tree
of life in a more exact way,

00:41:18.190 --> 00:41:21.300
you should think
that it's a network.

00:41:21.300 --> 00:41:28.090
The network in its old and
unicellular domains or regions

00:41:28.090 --> 00:41:31.870
has a sort of a somewhat
haphazard not really tree-like,

00:41:31.870 --> 00:41:33.880
but more complex structure.

00:41:33.880 --> 00:41:36.520
And in some groups,
especially animals,

00:41:36.520 --> 00:41:39.790
the thing sort of evolves
into a more definite tree

00:41:39.790 --> 00:41:42.490
where you have
two-way branchings

00:41:42.490 --> 00:41:49.430
and few or no rejoicings.

00:41:49.430 --> 00:41:53.350
So the full picture
is not quite a tree,

00:41:53.350 --> 00:41:56.090
but we animals, we form
a pretty good tree.

00:41:59.980 --> 00:42:00.960
OK.

00:42:00.960 --> 00:42:04.904
There's time for one more if
anyone would like to pop up.

00:42:12.680 --> 00:42:15.680
AUDIENCE: So you
had an illustration

00:42:15.680 --> 00:42:19.195
of the common ancestor of
the octopus and mammals.

00:42:22.700 --> 00:42:25.560
From my perspective when
I look at an octopus,

00:42:25.560 --> 00:42:29.480
it seems to have a lot of
similarities with mammals just

00:42:29.480 --> 00:42:31.970
in terms of the
level of advancement

00:42:31.970 --> 00:42:35.630
and complexity and
some things like you

00:42:35.630 --> 00:42:39.050
mentioned the design of
the eye are quite similar.

00:42:39.050 --> 00:42:42.260
How much of that
do you think was

00:42:42.260 --> 00:42:46.730
latent in the DNA
versus how much of that

00:42:46.730 --> 00:42:53.360
was truly independent because
it was required in the same way?

00:42:53.360 --> 00:42:56.630
Do you think that there
were independent mutations

00:42:56.630 --> 00:42:59.884
in the DNA that were
independently selected for?

00:42:59.884 --> 00:43:01.800
PETER GODFREY-SMITH:
It's a very good question

00:43:01.800 --> 00:43:03.470
and the word you
used, latent, I think

00:43:03.470 --> 00:43:07.220
is exactly the right
way to ask the question.

00:43:07.220 --> 00:43:10.460
So you have some
similarities of design

00:43:10.460 --> 00:43:12.770
in the present coming
from something that looks

00:43:12.770 --> 00:43:14.930
very different in the past.

00:43:14.930 --> 00:43:17.900
And there's a school
of thought in biology

00:43:17.900 --> 00:43:20.150
that I think would
answer your question

00:43:20.150 --> 00:43:21.324
with a kind of emphatic yes.

00:43:21.324 --> 00:43:22.490
They'd say, oh, yeah, right.

00:43:22.490 --> 00:43:24.020
They look very
different, but there

00:43:24.020 --> 00:43:26.750
was a kind of
architecture that was

00:43:26.750 --> 00:43:31.040
kind of latent in a way in the
first bilaterally symmetrical

00:43:31.040 --> 00:43:35.540
animals with a certain
kind of head to tail axis,

00:43:35.540 --> 00:43:38.060
a certain organization
of the relationship

00:43:38.060 --> 00:43:40.250
between the nervous
system and the rest.

00:43:40.250 --> 00:43:44.450
And you know you should
think of the subsequent

00:43:44.450 --> 00:43:49.370
unfolding down the two
lines as just variations

00:43:49.370 --> 00:43:53.600
on a theme in a way and a
theme that was set down early.

00:43:53.600 --> 00:43:55.372
That's one kind of
school of thought.

00:43:55.372 --> 00:43:57.080
I'm describing this
a bit metaphorically,

00:43:57.080 --> 00:43:59.716
I think it's clear in this case.

00:43:59.716 --> 00:44:01.340
Then there is another,
and in some ways

00:44:01.340 --> 00:44:03.590
more traditional school of
thought, that says, look,

00:44:03.590 --> 00:44:07.130
evolution can do anything it
pretty much wants with bodies.

00:44:07.130 --> 00:44:10.170
And you start with
something very simple,

00:44:10.170 --> 00:44:13.770
and the fact that you have
certain similarities here

00:44:13.770 --> 00:44:16.520
and here means that natural
selection disfavored

00:44:16.520 --> 00:44:19.580
similar things and there were
mutations occurring quite

00:44:19.580 --> 00:44:23.120
independently, quite
different in character

00:44:23.120 --> 00:44:25.460
that built a similar structure.

00:44:25.460 --> 00:44:29.240
Now, in the case of
having an eye with a lens,

00:44:29.240 --> 00:44:30.830
the second view is
certainly right.

00:44:30.830 --> 00:44:33.500
So there's no sense in
which the eye lens was

00:44:33.500 --> 00:44:36.680
latent in the common ancestor.

00:44:36.680 --> 00:44:39.840
And octopus lenses
and vertebrate lenses

00:44:39.840 --> 00:44:42.690
are built from different stuff,
they have a different role.

00:44:42.690 --> 00:44:46.870
So one distorts and one moves.

00:44:46.870 --> 00:44:50.330
So camera lenses don't
distort, they move.

00:44:50.330 --> 00:44:54.440
Some animal lenses distort, they
change shape, and some of them

00:44:54.440 --> 00:44:56.510
move.

00:44:56.510 --> 00:44:59.480
But the presence
of an eye at all

00:44:59.480 --> 00:45:02.660
in the animal, forget the lens
and the particular structure,

00:45:02.660 --> 00:45:05.720
but just whether you have
light sensitive things

00:45:05.720 --> 00:45:08.450
roughly where they are,
plenty of biologists

00:45:08.450 --> 00:45:11.810
think oh, yes, that
was probably laid down

00:45:11.810 --> 00:45:15.380
and it's not something that
was independently invented,

00:45:15.380 --> 00:45:17.750
it's something that
was laid down one time.

00:45:17.750 --> 00:45:21.970
So I mean, my
expertise, such as it

00:45:21.970 --> 00:45:24.800
is, is such that I can't
give a sort of richer

00:45:24.800 --> 00:45:27.890
answer to the question than
that because what you're putting

00:45:27.890 --> 00:45:31.220
your finger on there is a part
of biology which is intensely

00:45:31.220 --> 00:45:33.110
and actively debated
and there are

00:45:33.110 --> 00:45:34.835
different reasonable positions.

